The paper deals with problems related to finding tours and cycle covers in geometric graphs, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses complexity and approximation algorithms, which are topics in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of LP/IP techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also mentions practical applications, indicating that it may be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses graph theory and combinatorial optimization, which are topics in theoretical computer science (cs.GT).
